Experiment — Implementation of Semaphore and Multithreading

Aim
To implement semaphore and multithreading using pthreads in UNIX.

Algorithm
Initialize semaphore.
Create two threads using pthread_create().
Use sem_wait() to enter critical section.
Execute thread operation.
Use sem_post() to release semaphore.
Wait for threads using pthread_join().
Destroy semaphore.

Program

#include <stdio.h>
#include <pthread.h>
#include <semaphore.h>
#include <unistd.h>

sem_t s;

void* process(void* arg)
{
    sem_wait(&s);

    printf("Thread %ld entered Critical Section\n",
           (long)arg);

    sleep(2);

    printf("Thread %ld leaving Critical Section\n",
           (long)arg);

    sem_post(&s);

    return NULL;
}

int main()
{
    pthread_t t1, t2;

    sem_init(&s, 0, 1);

    pthread_create(&t1, NULL, process, (void*)1);
    pthread_create(&t2, NULL, process, (void*)2);

    pthread_join(t1, NULL);
    pthread_join(t2, NULL);

    sem_destroy(&s);

    return 0;
}


